  text: Your VBA line is evaluating a Boolean expression, which is why you get `FALSE`.

Problem line:
```vb
c.Value = ("C2") = Left(ws.Range("C2"), Len(ws.Range("C2")) - 3)
```

What this does is:

- `("C2") = Left(...)` compares the text `"C2"` to the result of `Left(...)`
- that comparison returns `True` or `False`
- then you assign that Boolean result to `c.Value`

So every cell gets `FALSE` unless the shortened postcode literally equals `"C2"`.

